(Adaptive Sparse Attention for Efficient Vision-Language Models) Tj
0 -24 Td
() Tj
0 -24 Td
(Abstract: We present a sparse attention strategy that reduces compute while preserving multimodal reasoning accuracy.) Tj
0 -24 Td
(Problem: Large vision-language models are expensive to train and hard to deploy for real-time conference demos.) Tj
0 -24 Td
(Method: Our method introduces adaptive token pruning with cross-modal routing in a lightweight transformer stack.) Tj
0 -24 Td
(Architecture: \(1\) Encode visual and text tokens. \(2\) Compute saliency gates. \(3\) Route high-value tokens through sparse attention.) Tj
0 -24 Td
(Result: On benchmark tasks, inference latency drops by 34% while accuracy remains within 1.2 points of dense baselines.) Tj
0 -24 Td
(Impact: The approach enables practical on-device multimodal assistants for education, healthcare, and accessibility workflows.) Tj
